### L3 — Handoff: Transfer context to a different agent
### SPEC §8.6
### Use case: the planning agent finishes; it hands off to the booking agent.
### The booking agent receives the full context with a bridge message.

POST /v1/sbp/sessions/a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890/handoff HTTP/1.1
Host: localhost:8080
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <your-api-key>

{
  "to_agent_id": "booking-agent-prod",
  "handoff_message": "The user has approved a 3-day Tokyo itinerary. Please proceed to book flights (SFO→NRT, May 20–23) and hotel (Shinjuku area, budget: $200/night). User preferences: window seat, vegetarian meals.",
  "reason": "Planning phase complete; booking phase begins."
}

### Response — HTTP 201

HTTP/1.1 201 Created
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "source_session_id": "a1b2c3d4-e5f6-7890-abcd-ef1234567890",
  "new_session_id":    "e5f6a7b8-c9d0-1234-efab-345678901234",
  "new_session_token": "tok_booking_xyz789",
  "to_agent_id":       "booking-agent-prod",
  "export_id":         "f6a7b8c9-d0e1-2345-fab c-456789012345"
}
